    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix scheduling priority inversion in EMM procedure initialization\n\n### Summary\nThere is a scheduling priority inversion where lower-priority traffic is served before higher-priority downstream of function _emm_detach_initialize in openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/emm_main.c.\n\nThe EMM main initialization function was setting up detach procedure data before attach procedure data. Since attach procedures typically have higher priority than detach procedures in mobile networks (establishing connectivity is more critical than disconnecting), this created a priority inversion scenario.\n\nThis fix reorders the initialization sequence to ensure higher-priority attach procedures are initialized before lower-priority detach procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/emm_main.c`: Swapped initialization order of attach and detach procedure data in emm_main_initialize function. Attach data is now initialized before detach data.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions where both attach and detach procedures are queued simultaneously, the incorrect initialization order could cause the detach procedure to be processed before the attach procedure, potentially leading to delayed network registration or connectivity issues when the UE needs to re-establish connection.\n\nUsers may observe intermittent connection establishment delays when the UE transitions from idle to connected state, particularly in scenarios involving periodic tracking area updates or network handovers that trigger both detach and attach procedures.\n"
}